title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Calculate the revenue loss for small-quantity orders for parts of brand ‘Brand#23’ and container type ‘MED BOX’ during the year 1996. A small order is defined as a lineitem whose quantity is less than 20% of the average quantity for that part. Compute the total gross (undiscounted) revenue of these small orders for the year 1996 and output the result in a textfile.

operations.table: (SELECT l_partkey, l_quantity, l_extendedprice, l_shipdate FROM lineitem) as X

operations.udf: (r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val pk = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val q = r.getField(1).asInstanceOf[Double]; val ep = r.getField(2).asInstanceOf[Double]; val sd = r.getField(3).toString; (pk, q, ep, sd) }
(a: (Int, Double, Double, String), b: (Int, Double, Double, String)) => (a._1, a._2 + b._2, a._3 + b._3, a._4)

(r: org.apache.wayang.basic.data.Record) => { val partKey = r.getField(0).asInstanceOf[Int]; val avgQty = r.getField(1).asInstanceOf[Double] / (r.getField(2).asInstanceOf[Double]); (partKey, avgQty) }

operations.table: (SELECT p_partkey, p_brand, p_container FROM part) as X

operations.udf: (t: ((Int, Double), (Int, String, String))) => { val pbrand = t._2._2; val pcont = t._2._3; pbrand == "Brand#23" && pcont == "MED BOX" }

log.thoughts: Plan loads lineitems and computes per-part average quantity, filters for Brand#23 with MED BOX, joins with lineitems to identify small orders (quantity < 20% of avg per part) shipped in 1996, sums their undiscounted revenue (l_extendedprice), and outputs the total to a text file.
